abstract: Study published in journal Reproductive Sciences suggests PP13 protein may play key role in development of pre-eclampsia, form of high blood pressure in pregnancy that strains mother's kidneys;.
snippet: Scientists have proposed a novel hypothesis to explain how a pregnant woman develops a serious condition called pre-eclampsia.
lead_paragraph: Scientists have proposed a novel hypothesis to explain how a pregnant woman develops a serious condition called pre-eclampsia.
